"536","    <div style=DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25><br></div>"
"537","    <div style=DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt align=justify><font style=DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman, serif>The"
"538","Shareholders and</font></div>"
"539","    <div style=DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt align=justify><font style=DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman, serif>Board"
"540","of Directors of Mairs and Power Balanced Fund, Inc.</font></div>"
"541","    <div style=DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25><br></div>"
"542","    <div style=DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt align=justify><font style=DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman, serif>In"
"543","planning and performing our audit of the financial statements of the Mairs and"
"544","Power Balanced Fund, Inc. (the Fund) as of and for the year ended December 31,"
"545","2009, in accordance with the standards of the Public Company Accounting"
"546","Oversight Board (United States), we considered the Fund&#8217;s internal control over"
"547","financial reporting, including controls over safeguarding securities, as a basis"
"548","for designing our auditing procedures for the purpose of expressing our opinion"
"549","on the financial statements and to comply with the requirements of Form N-SAR,"
"550","but not for the purpose of expressing an opinion on the effectiveness of the"
"551","Fund&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting. Accordingly, we express no"
"552","such opinion.</font></div>"
"553","    <div style=DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25><br></div>"
"554","    <div style=DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt align=justify><font style=DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman, serif>The"
"555","management of the Fund is responsible for establishing and maintaining effective"
"556","internal control over financial reporting. In fulfilling this responsibility,"
"557","estimates and judgments by management are required to assess the expected"
"558","benefits and related costs of controls. The Fund&#8217;s internal control over"
"559","financial reporting is a process designed to provide reasonable assurance"
"560","regarding the reliability of financial reporting and the preparation of"
"561","financial statements for external purposes in accordance with generally accepted"
"562","accounting principles. A Fund&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting"
"563","includes those policies and procedures that (1) pertain to the maintenance of"
"564","records that, in reasonable detail, accurately and fairly reflect the"
"565","transactions and dispositions of the assets of the Fund; (2) provide reasonable"
"566","assurance that transactions are recorded as necessary to permit preparation of"
"567","financial statements in accordance with generally accepted accounting"
"568","principles, and that receipts and expenditures of the Fund are being made only"
"569","in accordance with authorizations of management and directors of the Fund; and"
"570","(3) provide reasonable assurance regarding prevention or timely detection of"
"571","unauthorized acquisition, use or disposition of a Fund&#8217;s assets that could have"
"572","a material effect on the financial statements.</font></div>"
"573","    <div style=DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25><br></div>"
"574","    <div style=DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt align=justify><font style=DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman, serif>Because"
"575","of its inherent limitations, internal control over financial reporting may not"
"576","prevent or detect misstatements. Also, projections of any evaluation of"
"577","effectiveness to future periods are subject to the risk that controls may become"
"578","inadequate because of changes in conditions, or that the degree of compliance"
"579","with the policies or procedures may deteriorate.</font></div>"
"580","    <div style=DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25><br></div>"
"581","    <div style=DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt align=justify><font style=DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman, serif>A"
"582","deficiency in internal control over financial reporting exists when the design"
"583","or operation of a control does not allow management or employees, in the normal"
"584","course of performing their assigned functions, to prevent or detect"
"585","misstatements on a timely basis. A material weakness is a deficiency, or a"
"586","combination of deficiencies, in internal control over financial reporting, such"
"587","that there is a reasonable possibility that a material misstatement of the"
"588","Fund&#8217;s annual or interim financial statements will not be prevented or detected"
"589","on a timely basis.</font></div>"
"590","    <div style=DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25><br></div><br>"
"591","    <div id=PGBRK style=MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt>"
